label: Image Width
rdfs_comment: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid width of the meaningful image shall be recorded in this tag, whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker.  This tag shall not exist in an uncompressed file.
skos_scopeNote: The width in pixels of the media specified by the access point. Contrary to the definition, in Audiovisual Core, this term MAY be used with uncompressed files.
dcterms_description: Audiovisual Core uses this term for any image type, including those to which EXIF does not apply and those that are not a compressed file type like JPEG.

label: Image Height
rdfs_comment: Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded, the valid height of the meaningful image shall be recorded in this tag, whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker.  This tag shall not exist in an uncompressed file.
skos_scopeNote: The height in pixels of the media specified by the access point. Contrary to the definition, in Audiovisual Core, this term MAY be used with uncompressed files.
dcterms_description: Audiovisual Core uses this term for any image type, including those to which EXIF does not apply and those that are not a compressed file type like JPEG.

label: Image Length
rdfs_comment: Dimensions: The number of rows of image data. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is used
dcterms_description:
Use this term in combination with these other AC terms -- i.e., when: 
- ac:3DResourceType is any subtype that is encoded as a raster format
- and dc:format(s) is any raster format
- and ac:resourceCreationTechnique(s) is any of: CT, MRI, PET, Neutron, Synchrotron, confocal microscopy, optical image stacking, photogrammetry

label: Image Width
rdfs_comment: Dimensions: The number of columns of image data, equal to the number of pixels per row. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is used instead of this tag
dcterms_description:
Use this term in combination with these other AC terms -- i.e., when: 
- ac:3DResourceType is a subtype that is encoded as a raster format
- and dc:format(s) is any raster formats
- and ac:resourceCreationTechnique(s) is any of: CT, MRI, PET, Neutron, Synchotron, confocal microscopy, optical image stacking, photogrammetry
